Week 4 - BBO Capstone Project

Week 3's Strategy Discussion and Strategy Modifications for Week 4, based on Week 3 Query Outcomes:

For Function 1, Week 3's strategy (Matern kernel with nu=1.5 - because Function 1 is spiky - with applied Automatic Relevance Determination 
(ARD) with aggresive baseline and wider bounds, Sobol sampling and Thompson Sampling) worked the best so far, as the query submitted for 
Week 3 gave an output that shows the greatest improvement obtained so far in terms of maximisation. The obtained output for week 3 
(4.363936459722764e-23) has not yet exceeded the highest output within Function 1's dataset, but it is very close to it 
(7.710875114502849e-16). Therefore, for week 4, the same strategy as in Week 3 will be used, which uses Thompson sampling to check if 
any improvement is achieved. If the output for Week 4 will still be similar to Week 3's output, an Expected Improvement (EI) acquisition 
function will be used instead of Thompson sampling next time (Week 5). 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For Function 2, Week 3's query gave a very low output (0.09573287982128298), therefore Week 3's strategy for Function 2 (using Automatic 
Relevance Determination (ARD) with aggressive baseline - length_scale=[0.1]*3 - on the RBF kernel and wider length_scale_bounds=(1e-6, 1e8), 
Sobol sampling and Thompson sampling instead of UCB/EI) will not be pursued anymore. The best strategy implemented for query prediction so 
far for Function 2 has been Week 2's strategy (using Automatic Relevance Determination (ARD) on the RBF kernel with aggressive baseline - 
length_scale=[0.1]*2 - and wider length_scale_bounds=(1e-6, 1e8), Sobol sampling and UCB acquisition function, with beta = 1.96). However, 
because Week 2's strategy still did not predict a query point for Function 2 whose output exceeded all outputs within the dataset for this 
function, or be very close to it, a slightly modified strategy will be used this time for Week 4: using Automatic Relevance Determination 
(ARD) on the RBF kernel with aggressive baseline - length_scale=[0.1]*2 - and wider length_scale_bounds=(1e-6, 1e8), Sobol sampling and 
Expected Improvement (EI) acqusiiton function, with xi = 0.1 (large), to encourage exploration since this is still an early stage of the 
Black-Box fucntion optimisation (which is Week 2's strategy with EI instead of UCB as the acquisition function).

